00:51:37.500 --> 00:51:42.210
I think the critical
factor for everyone

00:51:42.210 --> 00:51:44.910
is to be well calibrated.

00:51:44.910 --> 00:51:49.440
You need to know about
yourself-- how defensive

00:51:49.440 --> 00:51:52.700
or how enterprising
am I prepared to be?

00:51:52.700 --> 00:51:58.580
And how qualified do I feel
to become enterprising?

00:51:58.580 --> 00:52:00.750
If you're not
comfortable with it,

00:52:00.750 --> 00:52:04.240
or you've done a
reasonable analysis

00:52:04.240 --> 00:52:08.080
and you can't get comfortable
that you could ever

00:52:08.080 --> 00:52:11.620
assess the probabilities, then
you should stay defensive.

00:52:11.620 --> 00:52:14.440
Now, being defensive
in Graham's terms

00:52:14.440 --> 00:52:18.300
doesn't mean that your
portfolio should all be cash.

00:52:18.300 --> 00:52:21.030
It just means you're
not going to analyze

00:52:21.030 --> 00:52:22.170
individual securities.

00:52:22.170 --> 00:52:25.100
You could put all your money
in stocks if you wanted to,

00:52:25.100 --> 00:52:28.690
and putting it in index funds is
a perfectly defensible choice,

00:52:28.690 --> 00:52:33.910
and a classic defensive choice.

00:52:33.910 --> 00:52:36.720
I would add one
