00:53:15.900 --> 00:53:17.360
I'm going to add more.

00:53:17.360 --> 00:53:20.440
So one way you can
be enterprising

00:53:20.440 --> 00:53:24.010
is you could be enterprising
with a defensive portfolio.

00:53:24.010 --> 00:53:26.310
You could say, the
next time there's

00:53:26.310 --> 00:53:30.370
a financial crisis or a crash,
and there will be one probably

00:53:30.370 --> 00:53:34.220
sooner rather than later--
although I have no idea when.

00:53:34.220 --> 00:53:38.420
But the next time there's a
market panic, you could say,

00:53:38.420 --> 00:53:41.530
I'm going to add a
substantial amount of money

00:53:41.530 --> 00:53:43.710
to my portfolio.

00:53:43.710 --> 00:53:46.150
Now, you don't have to do that.

00:53:46.150 --> 00:53:50.040
And the next crash might
be the final crash,

00:53:50.040 --> 00:53:52.730
and it might turn out
not to be a good idea.

00:53:52.730 --> 00:53:56.020
But if history is
any guide, people

00:53:56.020 --> 00:54:00.770
who take that step in
times of extreme disruption

00:54:00.770 --> 00:54:02.960
tend to do very well
in the long run.

