00:59:30.860 --> 00:59:34.370
of what the cognitive
errors were,

00:59:34.370 --> 00:59:37.130
the analytical errors
that professional money

00:59:37.130 --> 00:59:38.670
managers made.

00:59:38.670 --> 00:59:46.770
But I do think that what often
happens in situations like this

00:59:46.770 --> 00:59:49.793
is-- and I'm speaking
in general terms

00:59:49.793 --> 00:59:53.550
because I haven't done any
direct research on Valeant,

00:59:53.550 --> 00:59:56.610
and I haven't spoken
directly about it with many

00:59:56.610 --> 00:59:58.690
of the investors
you're referring,

00:59:58.690 --> 01:00:00.250
so I'm just speculating.

01:00:00.250 --> 01:00:04.600
But I think in
many cases, people

01:00:04.600 --> 01:00:08.250
rely on the assurances
of management

01:00:08.250 --> 01:00:18.320
and let qualitative factors
skew judgments that otherwise

01:00:18.320 --> 01:00:20.480
would be quantitatively based.

01:00:20.480 --> 01:00:24.980
And as an investor,
you always have

01:00:24.980 --> 01:00:29.280
to be very sensitive
to retroactive

01:00:29.280 --> 01:00:34.370
revisions of the reason
you own a security.

01:00:34.370 --> 01:00:41.950
If originally you invested
based on quantitative measures,

01:00:41.950 --> 01:00:45.330
and you now find
that you're using

01:00:45.330 --> 01:00:49.910
qualitative justifications
for continuing to hold it,

01:00:49.910 --> 01:00:51.660
then that is a red flag.

01:00:51.660 --> 01:00:55.870
And certainly one
of the things I've

01:00:55.870 --> 01:00:58.670
learned over the past
decade is the importance

01:00:58.670 --> 01:01:03.690
of having a structured
decision process

01:01:03.690 --> 01:01:09.940
and working off a checklist
or another template that

01:01:09.940 --> 01:01:14.460
compels you to organize your
thinking and your rationale.

01:01:14.460 --> 01:01:18.050
And it also makes it harder
for you to migrate away

01:01:18.050 --> 01:01:19.750
from that over time.

01:01:19.750 --> 01:01:23.600
And I think what we'll
learn with hindsight

01:01:23.600 --> 01:01:27.780
is that many of these investors
bought the stock for one

01:01:27.780 --> 01:01:33.720
set of reasons, and then
held it for a different set,

01:01:33.720 --> 01:01:36.870
and that is always a
red flag in investing

01:01:36.870 --> 01:01:39.010
as it is in a lot of
other things in life.

01:01:39.010 --> 01:01:44.790
I mean, someone who married a
spouse for one set of reasons

01:01:44.790 --> 01:01:47.660
and then stays with the
spouse for another set

01:01:47.660 --> 01:01:51.140
is probably not likely to
have a very happy marriage.

01:01:51.140 --> 01:01:54.410
And the same thing applies in
the financial world, I think.

01:01:54.410 --> 01:01:54.910
Yes.

01:01:54.910 --> 01:01:55.780
